citation.case_name: Chicago & Northwestern R. Co. v. Osborne

html:
146 U.S. 354

13 S.Ct. 281

36 L.Ed. 1002

CHICAGO & N. W. RY. CO.
v.
OSBORNE. SAME v. JUNOD et al.

Nos. 1,238, 1,239.

December 5, 1892.

C. C. Nourse, for petitioners.

1

W. C. Goudy, opposed.

2

THE CHIEF JUSTICE.

3

The petitions for writs of certiorari to the circuit court of appeals for the eighth circuit are denied. McLish v. Roff, 141 U. S. 661, 12 Sup. Ct. Rep. 118; Rice v. Sanger, 144 U. S. 197, 12 Sup. Ct. Rep. 664; Meagher v. Manufacturing Co., 145 U. S. 608, 12 Sup. Ct. Rep. 876.

THE CHIEF JUSTICE: The petitions for writs of certiorari to the Circuit Court of Appeals for the eighth circuit are denied. McLish v. Roff, 141 U.S. 661; Rice v. Sanger, 144 U.S. 197; Meagher v. Minnesota Thresher Manufacturing Co., 145 U.S. 608.
